                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (strong red)</seg>The hand is very similar, or possibly even identical, to that of Ms. VatLib Aeth. 263 (Book of Isaiah, Ascension of Isaiah, Book of Daniel, s. LanVat 465, in which Ṣagā Matta [sic (Ṣagā Maṭāʿ?)] is indicated as possible scribe). 
                        On the dating of Aeth. 263, s. UhlPal.<date>Pre-1350 (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Titles of most of the texts are written on the incipit and repeated on the explicit pages; a few lines on the incipit pages of each texts alternating with black lines; 
                           elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; the words wa-nababo ʾǝgziʾa bǝḥer la-Muse (e.g., fols. 102va, 103vb, 105rb etc.); the words wa-yǝbelomu ʾǝgziʾa bǝḥer la-Muse(fol. 118vb); in some cases, zǝya-sign, fols. 122v, 124r</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Portions of the text appear to have been written in different hands, cp. <locus target="#27vb">27vb</locus>, 30v, 39ra, 66r-v, 74ra (possibly), 77v (possibly), 111vb, 127vb, 194vb, etc.
</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">Earlier hand of Additio 1</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic">Later hand of Additio 2</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
